# Results

## Testing Methodology
Testing of these structures is performed by using an AFM tip with stiff cantilever. The AFM allows sample imaging before and after the test, as well as accurate selection of the nanostructure to be tested and accurate positioning of the tip. The apparatus allows for the independent measurement of both the deformation and the applied force. 

A schematic of the test set-up is shown in Fig. 4. The AFM is used to obtain a topographical map of the surface. Then one selects a specimen to be loaded, the tip is positioned and brought in contact with the nanostructure. The vertical motion of the table is then controlled. The cantilever deflection is mapped to the force, while the deflection of the specimen results from the known motion of the table and the measured deflection of the cantilever.

