## Inelastic Deformation
Figure 6 shows the force-deflection curve measured for the structures in Fig. 3. These are made from amorphous Si, which is a nominally brittle material. However, here we observe pronounced inelastic behavior even before failure. If the sample is unloaded before the peak load, a residual deformation is measured. This indicates a brittle-to-ductile transition of the material when the specimen dimensions are reduced.

