## Material Response to Fatigue Loading
The specimens in Fig. 3 were tested under cyclic loading conditions to determine their fatigue life. Brittle materials are usually not susceptible to fatigue failure. However, life reduction is observed in small-scale structures made from brittle materials loaded a large number of cycles. Figure 7 shows a Wohler diagram for these specimens. The data points indicate failure of various specimens tested up to the specified load and number of cycles. As the applied load decreases, the number of cycles to failure increases.

